Upstream-Name: aiger
Upstream-Contact: Armin Biere <biere@jku.at>
Source: https://github.com/arminbiere/aiger
Comment: The AIGER library is a reader and writer for the AIGER AIG
 (And-Inverter Graph) format. The vendored copy consists of the two files
 aiger.c and aiger.h, and is used by src/aiger/ (the AIGER language
 front-end for EBMC).
 .
 The in-tree files are byte-for-byte identical to upstream commit
 a1b949aad00251a8493513301af660977fe6ee92 (2011-07-22). This is not a
 tagged release; it predates the rel-1.9.17 tag (2024-01-31), which is the
 earliest tag in the upstream repository. Later upstream revisions add
 extern "C" guards, const qualifiers on several function signatures, and
 additional utility functions (aiger_strip_symbols, aiger_strip_comments,
 aiger_is_constant).

